  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nWhen creating a block using `/validator/block` endpoint, the caller specifies the slot to create a block for.  \r\n\r\nIf this block is prior to our best head block, Teku will throw an exception `java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: process_slots: State slot higher than given slot` because we can't process slots backwards.\r\n\r\nIf the block is too far in the future, Teku may try to include attestations that are too old - they must be from either the same or previous epoch as the block being created:\r\n`tech.pegasys.artemis.statetransition.util.BlockProcessingException: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: process_attestations: Attestation not from current or previous epoch`.\r\n\r\nCurrently both of these result in a 500 Internal Server error. Need to understand if either of these cases should be supported correctly and either make it work or return a bad request response with a clear error.",
